= Introduction =
sfLucene integrates Zend_Search_Lucene and sfSearch for an efficient but powerful search engine.

Warning: This documentation is a work-in-progress and may be difficult to read. 

= Requirements =
  * symfony 1.1
  * PHP 5.2

= Dependencies =
  * [[sfSearchPlugin]]

= Installation =
sfLucene is currently available from subversion only:
{{{
svn co http://svn.symfony-project.com/plugins/sfLucenePlugin/trunk plugins/sfLucenePlugin 
}}}
You will also need [[sfSearchPlugin]]:
{{{
svn co http://svn.symfony-project.com/plugins/sfSearchPlugin/trunk plugins/sfSearchPlugin
}}}

= Usage =
To use sfLucene in sfSearch, configure the engine like so in your index:
{{{
protected function configure()
{
  // ...

  $engine = new xfLuceneEngine(sfConfig::get('sf_data_dir') . '/index/MyIndex');
  $engine->configure(xfLuceneEngine::ANALYZER_UTF8 | xfLuceneEngine::ANALYZER_NUMBER);
  
  $this->setEngine($engine);
}
}}}
